  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&quot;Early Recovery and Rehabilitation for the Cyclone Aila affected communities&quot;</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cyclone &quot;AILA&quot; hit the west border of Bangladesh on 25 May 2009.  AILA affected around 3.39 million people while more than 375,000 people have been displaced and are now living in temporary shelters. 290 deaths were recorded. Oxfam has received Euro 650 k from ECHO for initial response which has been ended 31 Dec&apos;09. Euro 514 k has been granted for further 12 months period by ECHO for early recovery and rehabilitation which will contribute to the Livelihoods recovery of the adult and adolescent women, men and children in &#x2018;Aila&apos; cyclone affected communities in Khulna and Shatkhira Districts.</narrative>
  </description>
